identified_by.content: PRJ/1/31 - Negatives and transparencies, partly identified

referred_to_by.content:
Negatives and small transparencies of b&w photographs of G.E. Street buildings, some by Paul Joyce and the rest probably by the architectural photographer Gordon Lansdown Barnes (c 1917-1985) [see Summary of Gordon Barnes's photography notebook, PRJ/8/3]. 35mm negatives and 2.25" x 3.25" transparencies.

Originally stored in glassine sleeves; Joyce identifed some of the buildings by labelling the sleeves, others were left blank. Labelled sleeves have been retained above the image. The sleeves are arranged alphabetically by location.

In January 2018 Geoff Brandwood identified some of the previously untitled images and this information has been added below.

It is likely prints of these photographs are present in the images files [PRJ/1/1-30].
